at|mitche:  Play:  At 1NT, the heart and heart continuation is perfectly reasonable.
North should put in the @h7, not the @hK 
Why?
Let's guess that East wins the 7 with the 8.  Another heart from East gives declarer 2 tricks, so East can't continue hearts.
And if West has a third heart and the @SA, then the defense would take the @DAK, the @SA, and 5 hearts
Ducking the heart, while not assuring the contract, makes it much more likely that declarer will succeed.
