at|mitche: Play: Declarer's plan should be to win 8 trumps and 2 outside aces. 
When the defense goes after trumps, declarer must try the @D finesse.  
If it loses, well, the hand will go down, but if declarer doesn't take the finesse, he goes down anyway.

